content: I've been trying to establish a consistent sleep schedule, but it's been tough. I've noticed that my sleep patterns tend to be affected by my daily commute. Since I leave the house at 8:45 AM to grab a coffee before my train ride, I'm wondering if I can use my commute time to help regulate my sleep schedule. Do you think listening to calming music or nature sounds during my commute could help signal to my body that it's time to wind down before bed?
